action-delete-dump: Button to delete dumps for the wiki.
action-generate-dump: Button to generate dumps for the wiki.
action-view-dump: Button to view dumps for the wiki.
datadump-cannot-delete: Displayed to user after trying to delete dump but due to status being anything other than completed or failed, it is not allowed. "Completed" is {{msg-mw|datadump-table-column-completed}} and "failed" is {{msg-mw|datadump-table-column-failed}}.
datadump-delete-failed: Displayed to user after trying to delete a dump but it fails.
datadump-delete-success: Displayed to user after successfully being able to delete a dump.
datadump-dump-does-not-exist: Displayed to the user indicating the dump does not exist.
datadump-generated-disabled: Displayed to user indicating dumps cannot be created due to it being disabled.
datadump-generated-error: Displayed to the user after trying to request a dump be generated, but there's a failure. $1 is the limit of allowed dumps.
datadump-generated-success: Displayed to the user after successfully requesting a dump.
datadump-label-generate:
Button label for the button to generate a data dump.
{{Identical|Generate}}
datadump-link: Link to [[Special:DataDump]] (data dump) in the sidebar toolbox, shown if the current user has managewiki user right.
datadump-no-results: Displayed to the user indicating no dumps have been found.
datadump-not-configured: Displayed to the user indicating the setting $wgDataDump has not been configured.
datadump-refresh: Link to [[Special:DataDump]] (data dump) to refresh the page.
datadump-type-invalid: Displayed to the user that the type for the dump that has been selected is not in the config.
log-name-datadump:
{{doc-logpage}}

The name of the datadump log.
